headline: Why Host Hotels & Resorts (HST) Is Up 8.1% After Doubling Net Income in Q3 2025
summary: Host Hotels & Resorts, Inc. recently reported its third-quarter 2025 earnings, posting US$1.33 billion in revenue and US$161 million in net income, both higher than the same quarter last year. An interesting highlight is that net income and earnings per share from continuing operations more than doubled year-over-year, signaling improved profitability despite analyst expectations of only marginal performance.
